did.abstract: As of 2017, John M. Bennet is an American experimental text, sound, and visual poet, active participant in the mail art community, and founder of Luna Bisonte Prods. The John M. Bennett Correspondence contains personal and professional correspondence sent and received by Bennet from 1969-2017, including mail art, poetry, and visual poems.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: As of 2017, John M. Bennet is an American experimental text, sound, and visual poet and active participant in the mail art community. Through his small press, Luna Bisonte Prods (founded in 1974), he prints small books, chapbooks, cards, pamphlets, artistsâ€™ books, audio and video works, and other avant garde works. Bennett was the editor of Lost and Found Times, published by Luna Bisonte Prods, from 1975-2005. Bennett was also curator of the Avant Writing Collection at the Ohio State University Libraries.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The John M. Bennett Correspondence contains personal and professional correspondence sent and received by Bennet from 1969-2017, including mail art, poetry, and visual poems. The collection contains correspondence from many avant garde writers and artists, including a large amount of correspondence from visual poets Gyorgy Kostritskii and Jim Leftwich, and correspondence from and about American mail artist and writer Blaster Al Ackerman with whom Bennett collaborated under the joint pen name of Jack A. Withers Smote.

In addition to correspondence, the collection also contains printouts of websites and blogs where Bennett's work appeared, printouts of conversations from internet message boards, compact discs, floppy discs, VHS cassettes, and publications from Luna Bisonte Prods.
